// =============================================================================
// AI-004: Sensitive Data Uploaded to Generative AI Services
// =============================================================================
// Author:      BlueRed Security (https://uaeblueredsecurity.com)
// Version:     1.0.0
// Platform:    Microsoft Defender XDR (Advanced Hunting)
// Tables:      CloudAppEvents (primary), DeviceNetworkEvents + DeviceFileEvents
//              (endpoint fallback, see commented block)
// Sentinel:    See AI-004-sensitive-data-to-genai.yaml for the scheduled
//              analytics rule version (uses TimeGenerated instead of Timestamp)
// MITRE:       T1567 (Exfiltration Over Web Service)
// =============================================================================
//
// PURPOSE
// Detects files uploaded from corporate identities into generative AI services.
// AI-001 answers "who is talking to AI"; this answers the harder question,
// "who is sending FILES to AI". A pasted paragraph is a policy issue; a whole
// contract, source tree or customer export uploaded into a consumer AI tier is
// a data-loss event with no DLP coverage and no contractual protection.
//
// TELEMETRY NOTE (read before deploying)
// Raw endpoint network tables cannot measure upload volume or file content, so
// this detection needs one of:
//   - Microsoft Defender for Cloud Apps (populates CloudAppEvents with file
//     upload actions and the destination app). This is the PRIMARY query below.
//   - Microsoft Purview Endpoint DLP (egress activity with destination), or a
//     CASB/proxy doing DLP on GenAI domains.
// Without one of those, use the ENDPOINT FALLBACK block at the bottom, which
// correlates a GenAI browser session with sensitive-file access in the same
// window. It is lower confidence (staging inference, not a confirmed upload).
//
// HOW TO USE
// 1. Confirm Defender for Cloud Apps is streaming CloudAppEvents.
// 2. Run the discovery query in the README to find the exact upload ActionType
//    strings and GenAI app names in YOUR tenant, then align the lists below.
// 3. Baseline over 7 days, then deploy on a 1h to 4h schedule.
//
// =============================================================================

let lookback = 24h;
// --- GenAI apps as they appear in Defender for Cloud Apps (Application) ------
let genai_apps = dynamic([
    "ChatGPT", "OpenAI", "Anthropic", "Claude",
    "Google Gemini", "Google Bard", "Gemini",
    "Perplexity", "DeepSeek", "Mistral AI", "Mistral",
    "Hugging Face", "Poe", "Character.AI", "Grammarly",
    "Copilot", "Microsoft Copilot"
]);
// --- GenAI hostnames, for tenants where the app resolves only by URL --------
let genai_domains = dynamic([
    "chatgpt.com", "openai.com", "claude.ai", "anthropic.com",
    "gemini.google.com", "perplexity.ai", "deepseek.com",
    "mistral.ai", "huggingface.co", "poe.com", "character.ai"
]);
// --- Upload-style actions (values vary by connected/discovered app) ----------
let upload_actions = dynamic([
    "FileUploaded", "FileUpload", "Upload", "FileUploadedToCloud",
    "EntityUploaded", "Put", "MessageAttachmentUploaded"
]);
CloudAppEvents
| where Timestamp > ago(lookback)
| where ActionType has_any (upload_actions)
| where Application has_any (genai_apps)
    or tostring(RawEventData) has_any (genai_domains)
| extend
    FileName = tostring(coalesce(ObjectName, tostring(RawEventData.ObjectName))),
    User = tostring(coalesce(AccountDisplayName, AccountObjectId)),
    App = Application
| summarize
    UploadCount = count(),
    FirstSeen = min(Timestamp),
    LastSeen = max(Timestamp),
    Apps = make_set(App, 10),
    Files = make_set(FileName, 25),
    Actions = make_set(ActionType, 10),
    SourceIPs = make_set(IPAddress, 10),
    DeviceTypes = make_set(DeviceType, 5),
    ReportIds = make_set(ReportId, 5)
    by User, AccountObjectId
| extend DistinctFileCount = array_length(Files)
| order by UploadCount desc
// =============================================================================
// OUTPUT: one row per user, listing every file sent to a GenAI app in the
// window, upload volume and source IPs. Prioritize rows with many distinct
// files or file names that look like exports, dumps or documents.
// =============================================================================
//
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// ENDPOINT FALLBACK (no Defender for Cloud Apps / DLP available)
// Lower confidence: it does not confirm an upload, it flags a GenAI browser
// session that coincides with sensitive-file access by the same user. Uncomment
// and run separately. Tune sensitive_paths / sensitive_ext to your environment.
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
